Still trending down.

35:31.397 --> 35:33.532
I'm gonna need
more cardiac support.

35:33.565 --> 35:35.167
Slam that blood into him.

35:58.224 --> 36:01.693
(alarms stop,
monitor beeping steadily)

36:01.727 --> 36:04.463
-Vitals are improving.

36:04.496 --> 36:07.032
KIT and MINA:
Show-off.

36:07.065 --> 36:09.034
AUSTIN:
Hey, if you got it, flaunt it.

36:09.067 --> 36:10.636
BELL:
As we were.

36:10.669 --> 36:14.206
AUSTIN:
#TeamChastain, baby.

36:14.240 --> 36:16.575
NOLAN:
Laurie's recovering.
You were right.

36:16.608 --> 36:18.510
Checking the abdomen
was a good call.

36:21.947 --> 36:24.850
-This thing has teeth.
-It has a tooth.

36:24.883 --> 36:27.553
It's a teratoma.
It's not gonna bite you, Ricky.

36:27.586 --> 36:29.988
Teratomas are genetic anomalies
that reproduce organs,

36:30.021 --> 36:32.924
or sometimes bone or teeth,
all within a pocket of flesh.

36:32.958 --> 36:34.326
NOLAN:
Rare. Unpleasant.

36:34.360 --> 36:35.327
Perfectly appropriate discovery

36:35.361 --> 36:37.062
on All Hallows' Eve.

36:37.095 --> 36:38.997
Some teratomas create antibodies
that attack the brain,

36:39.030 --> 36:40.399
and this can lead
to encephalitis.

36:40.432 --> 36:42.033
-They can.
-We'll rerun her CSF panel

36:42.067 --> 36:45.571
for Anti-NMDA antibodies.

36:45.604 --> 36:47.606
I think we got this.

36:52.210 --> 36:53.579
Okay, that's enough.

37:04.256 --> 37:06.425
I'm really gonna be okay?

37:06.458 --> 37:08.226
Yes. Yes!

37:12.831 --> 37:16.201
Yeah. You have
Anti-NMDA encephalitis.

37:16.234 --> 37:17.736
It's a rare infection
of the brain.

37:17.769 --> 37:19.405
It was causing
all your symptoms.

37:19.438 --> 37:20.872
We're gonna give you
a combination

37:20.906 --> 37:22.474
of steroids and immunoglobulins.

37:22.508 --> 37:24.042
Your night terrors might persist
for a bit, but

37:24.075 --> 37:26.612
you should be back
to your normal life in no time.

37:26.645 --> 37:28.614
Ah. I haven't
spoken to my family

37:28.647 --> 37:32.551
in two years, but right now...

37:32.584 --> 37:34.820
can't wait to tell them
I'm gonna be okay.

37:34.853 --> 37:37.589
I just hope
they pick up the phone.

37:37.623 --> 37:38.990
Family is complicated.

37:39.024 --> 37:41.092
You just have to hope

37:41.126 --> 37:43.261
that they'll be there
for you in the end.

37:55.140 --> 37:57.643
You were right.

37:57.676 --> 38:01.279
I should string a few days
together, recharge my batteries.

38:01.313 --> 38:04.616
-Just say the word.
-I will.

38:04.650 --> 38:06.352
When you tell me the truth.

38:06.385 --> 38:08.520
Where were you today?

38:11.823 --> 38:14.259
Maybe when you stop lying to me,

38:14.292 --> 38:16.528
I'll consider going
to an island with you.

38:16.562 --> 38:20.131
Sharing everything all the time

38:20.165 --> 38:22.501
is not something
I'm interested in.

38:22.534 --> 38:24.770
Well, I am.

38:24.803 --> 38:26.638
Son, I'm a lot of things,

38:26.672 --> 38:29.375
but a hypocrite
isn't one of them.

38:29.408 --> 38:31.677
What's that supposed to mean?

38:31.710 --> 38:33.712
I'm not exactly sitting

38:33.745 --> 38:36.348
across from an open book.

38:36.382 --> 38:39.785
You left home and didn't tell me
where you were for ten years.

38:39.818 --> 38:42.988
I had to hire a private
investigator to track you down.

38:43.021 --> 38:46.191
So don't ask of me

38:46.224 --> 38:50.195
what you refuse
to ask of yourself.

38:54.165 --> 38:56.101
Get some rest.

39:10.215 --> 39:12.250
KIT:
Welcome back, Frank.

39:15.554 --> 39:17.589
What... what happened to me?

39:17.623 --> 39:20.025
Wee bit of a car accident.

39:20.058 --> 39:22.994
Dr. Voss and I were part
of the team that reattached

39:23.028 --> 39:25.931
your arm and your leg.

39:25.964 --> 39:27.733
Did

39:27.766 --> 39:29.768
Couple of times.

39:29.801 --> 39:32.538
The important thing
is you're here now.

39:32.571 --> 39:35.574
Yeah, m

39:35.607 --> 39:38.276
And daughters?

39:38.309 --> 39:40.412
Do

39:40.446 --> 39:44.249
Yeah. They're on their way
